VAfter I graduated from MIT,
p46
aVI went to work for Digital Equipment Corporation.
p47
aVAt DEC, I worked on software
p48
aVfor the new area of computerized typesetting.
p49
aVI helped newspapers replace their reporters' typewriters
p50
aVwith computer terminals.
p51
aVI'd write software
p52
aVand then I'd go out in the field to places like the Kansas City Star,
p53
aVwhere I would train users and get feedback.
