aa(lp101
VSo, sitting there with 87 other people in the class, I got to daydream a lot.
p102
aVMost programmers in those days worked on mainframes,
p103
aVbuilding things like inventory systems, payroll systems and bill-paying systems.
p104
aVBut I had worked on interactive word processing
p105
aVand on-demand personal computation.
p106
aVInstead of thinking about paper printouts and punch cards,
p107
aVI imagined a magic blackboard
p108
aVthat if you erased one number and wrote a new thing in,
p109
aVall of the other numbers would automatically change,
p110
aVlike word processing with numbers.
p111
aVI imagined that my calculator had mouse hardware on the bottom of it
p112
aVand a head-up display, like in a fighter plane.
p113
aVAnd I could type some numbers in, and circle it, and press the sum button.
p114
aVAnd right in the middle of a negotiation I'd be able to get the answer.
